  "steps": [
    {
      "step": 0,
      "narration": "Let's find the derivative of f of x equals x cubed plus two x squared minus five x plus one.",
      "latex": "f(x) = x^{3} + 2x^{2} - 5x + 1",
      "audio_path": "/Users/claudioatlas/Desktop/Orbital/orbital_factory/jobs/2488e575/audio/step_00.mp3",
      "duration": 7.48
    },
    {
      "step": 1,
      "narration": "We'll use the power rule for derivatives. The power rule says that the derivative of x to the n is n times x to the n minus one.",
      "latex": "\\frac{d}{dx}(x^{n}) = nx^{n-1}",
      "audio_path": "/Users/claudioatlas/Desktop/Orbital/orbital_factory/jobs/2488e575/audio/step_01.mp3",
      "duration": 9.01
    },
    {
      "step": 2,
      "narration": "Let's apply the power rule to each term separately, starting with x cubed.",
      "latex": "\\frac{d}{dx}(x^{3}) = 3x^{2}",
      "audio_path": "/Users/claudioatlas/Desktop/Orbital/orbital_factory/jobs/2488e575/audio/step_02.mp3",
      "duration": 4.69
    },
    {
      "step": 3,
      "narration": "Next, the derivative of two x squared is two times the derivative of x squared.",
      "latex": "\\frac{d}{dx}(2x^{2}) = 2 \\cdot 2x^{1} = 4x",
      "audio_path": "/Users/claudioatlas/Desktop/Orbital/orbital_factory/jobs/2488e575/audio/step_03.mp3",
      "duration": 5.43
    },
    {
      "step": 4,
      "narration": "For negative five x, remember that x is x to the first power.",
      "latex": "\\frac{d}{dx}(-5x) = -5 \\cdot 1x^{0} = -5",
      "audio_path": "/Users/claudioatlas/Desktop/Orbital/orbital_factory/jobs/2488e575/audio/step_04.mp3",
      "duration": 4.69
    },
    {
      "step": 5,
      "narration": "Finally, the derivative of a constant like one is always zero.",
      "latex": "\\frac{d}{dx}(1) = 0",
      "audio_path": "/Users/claudioatlas/Desktop/Orbital/orbital_factory/jobs/2488e575/audio/step_05.mp3",
      "duration": 4.27
    },
    {
      "step": 6,
      "narration": "Now let's put all these derivatives together.",
      "latex": "f'(x) = 3x^{2} + 4x - 5 + 0",
      "audio_path": "/Users/claudioatlas/Desktop/Orbital/orbital_factory/jobs/2488e575/audio/step_06.mp3",
      "duration": 2.83
    },
    {
      "step": 7,
      "narration": "We can simplify by removing the plus zero, giving us our final answer.",
      "latex": "f'(x) = 3x^{2} + 4x - 5",
      "audio_path": "/Users/claudioatlas/Desktop/Orbital/orbital_factory/jobs/2488e575/audio/step_07.mp3",
      "duration": 4.69
    }
  ]
}